==English==
===Etymology===
Probably of Scandinavian origin, compare Danish [[dvale]] ‘dead sleep, stupor’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /dweɪl/

===Noun===
'''dwale'''
# a [[sleeping-potion]], especially one made from [[belladonna]]
#:*'''Late C14''': To bedde goþ Aleyne and also John; / Þer nas na moore – hem nedede no dwale. — Geoffrey Chaucer, ''The Reeve's Tale''
# [[belladonna]] itself, deadly nightshade; or other soporific plant